frameDefinitions: This frame is about Items in the state of occupying a certain Rank within a hierarchy.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
In this frame, there is a Part of a Whole in which the Part is defined with respect to the canonical or inherent orientation of the Whole.

An Item is located at the top end of a scale of importance or social rank (or some other Attribute) in comparison to other members of a Contrast_set (usually, implicit) that is otherwise similar in kind to the Item.
A Speaker communicates a message stating an Item's membership in a Category, i.e., asserts that the Item has the defining characteristics of the Category.
The Focal_feature is defined in relation to a Landmark_feature, either as a particular part, or as an immediately bordering entity.
frameExamples: He <t>ranks</t> second in his class in mathematics.
The <t>main</t> problem is that the administration has not yet clarified 'Regime change.' INI
He <t>depicted</t> his involvement as merely peripheral.
I'm on the <t>summit</t> of Mt. Shasta.
listRoleDefinitions: The Item which occupies the Rank in the hierarchy.
The dimension along which the ranking is defined.
The time at which/period over which the <fen>Item</fen> occupies the <fen>Rank</fen>
The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.
An <fen>Item</fen> is the foremost thing in the <fen>Contrast_set</fen>.
This role identifies the domain (usually temporally or spatially defined) within which the <fen>Item</fen> is primary among its kind.
The <fen>Contrast_set</fen> is a group of entities similar to the <fen>Item</fen> out of which the <fen>Item</fen> is the most preeminent.
The individual that communicates the message concerning the <fen>Category</fen> of an <fen>Item</fen>.
The class of entities with characteristics that match those of the <fen>Item</fen> according to the portrayal of the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Speaker</fen> portrays as belonging to a <fen>Category</fen>.
The piece of text in which a <fen>Speaker</fen> communicates their categorization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The point in time at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes a characterization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> characterizes the <fen>Item</fen>
A stable bounded area defined by its relation to another landform. This role is incorporated in each LU in this frame.
The landform with respect to which the <fen>Focal_feature</fen> is defined.
listRoleExamples: He ranks second in his class <fex>in mathematics</fex>.
Jim ranked as thirty-second degree Mason <fex>in 1970</fex>.
The top <fex>shelf</fex> of the bookcase was lying on the floor.
The show takes place in the West wing <fex>of the White House</fex>.
The foremost band <fex>in the world of the 1960's</fex> was clearly the Beatles.
Our discussion has raised a number of issues, foremost <fex>among them</fex> time.
However, <fex>'A Brief History of Medicine'</fex> characterizes influenza as the most deadly plague, overall.
